        },
        "subject": "LU-1866 ldiskfs: allow dotdot to be updated with data appended",
        "message": "LU-1866 ldiskfs: allow dotdot to be updated with data appended\n\nThe original implementation assumed that there was enough space\nto hold dotdot entry for rename. It is not always true when new\nname entry has extra data appended, such as FID-in-dirent, but\nold name entry has not. The old patch may cause directory crash.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ie921c8e9cf1ce7ef25789272fa5c8c85905d7e10\n"
      },
